TEED Hub Project – Initial Design & UX Documentation
1. Core Principles

Mobile-First:

Every page is designed starting with small screens (phones).

Responsive breakpoints scale up to tablets, desktops, and wide screens.

Tailwind’s responsive utilities (sm:, md:, lg:) will be used from day one.

Modern & Fancy UX:

Minimalist yet visually striking (like Stripe, Notion, or Linear).

Smooth animations for transitions, buttons, hover effects.

Clear hierarchy of content with whitespace, typography, and color accents.

Multi-Portal for Customers:

Each user will have a personal dashboard.

Includes sections for:

Business analytics (sales, growth charts)

Social tools (post generators, growth trackers)

Account & subscription management

Modular design: each “widget” or section is a React component for reusability.

Simple, Intuitive Navigation:

Top navigation bar or sidebar depending on screen size.

Sticky navigation for dashboards.

Icons + text for clarity.

Design System & Branding:

Brand color: #1F75FE (primary)

Secondary palette: subtle grays, whites, and accent colors.

Font system: modern sans-serif (Inter, System UI)

Use Tailwind + shadcn/ui for consistent components.

2. Suggested Page & Component Structure

Folders

/src
 ├─ /assets       # images, icons, fonts
 ├─ /components   # reusable UI pieces (cards, buttons, charts)
 ├─ /pages        # each page (Home, Dashboard, Login, Settings, etc)
 ├─ /layouts      # Layout components (Header, Footer, Sidebar)
 ├─ /api          # Axios instances
 ├─ /i18n         # translations


Page Examples

Home → Landing page / teaser

Dashboard → User portal (charts, analytics, shortcuts)

SocialTools → Growth tools (Instagram, Facebook, Google listings)

Payments → Subscription, wallet, transactions

Account → Profile, security, settings

Component Examples

Card, StatWidget, Chart, Sidebar, Header, Button, Modal, Table

3. Design / Style Guidelines

Spacing & Layout

Use Tailwind spacing utilities consistently: p-4, m-4, space-x-2, space-y-4.

Grids for dashboard cards: grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6.

Typography

Headings: text-2xl → text-5xl depending on hierarchy

Body: text-base → text-lg

Font-weight: semi-bold for headings, normal for body

Colors & Dark Mode

Primary: #1F75FE

Background: light mode → #FFFFFF, dark mode → #111827

Cards: light gray in light mode, darker gray in dark mode

Text: high contrast for readability

Animations

Button hover: subtle shadow or color transition

Loading states: skeleton components

Charts: animated transitions

Responsiveness

Mobile: single column layouts, collapsible sidebar

Tablet: 2–3 column cards

Desktop: 4+ column grid for dashboard

